This paper deals with optimizing the K nearest neighbors (KNN) search, which is a common problem in databases and machine learning. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of GPU and CPU architectures, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach using real-world datasets, which is relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
